<br />

<br />
Retire him.  You sir were not meant to play a bard.  
<br />

<br />
If you think that all the class is good for is AOE kiting, and that not AOE kiting means you cannot play a bard, then you probably cannot play a bard with the rest of what we can do.  If you don't appreciate the breadth of the bard class, then don't bother playing it.  If you can't transform a group, or a raid, into something greater... you aren't a bard.  Soloing methods are just there to pound in the XPs for what we REALLY do.
<br />

<br />
AOE kiting is hard.  Many good bards never master it.  Many that master it are not good bards.  Some use it to make their good bards that much better.  Many that CAN do it, don't bother because its a hassle and a frustration at times.  Yes its rockin XPs if you do it well, but it can be both stressful and boring (a bad mix), and repeated deaths are not uncommon.  All these truths are overshadowed by this one:  One-trick-pony bards suck... if thats what you aspire to be... retire.</span></td>
