				<td colspan="2"><span>Autocircle is the &quot;DEBIL!&quot;  Do not auto circle it is not worth the hassle and in the end if you do a raid where you need to do crowd control you just simply cannot ac those mobs<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  
<br />

<br />
I do not consider myself a great bard, I am average at best, but I like the complexities involved.  It is nice to be able to do so much for so many in groups, and who hates bard run right<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />  kiting takes alot of practice and patience and yes deaths too, even the best get lag, or miss a timed turn or gets too anxious, hehe or once with me falls alseep<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-4.gif" border="0" alt="Tongue out" hspace="2" /> the main thing is to find a way to stay ahead of the mobs but not out of song range, also not to make it too tiresome on you too.  If you could have run3 at earlier than level 51 or so it would be perfect but I suggest getting yourself some jboots for unlimited intant 18minute cast of a reduced sow.  It will give you the speed you need, but not too much and it is just enough to only make you slowly outrun your mobs, which will just catch up with you during your turns.  Play with your paths too.  Try long ovals, firgure 8's or for I do triangles.  When I kite I do a 3 point triangle.  If they hit me I widen my agles instead of turning too sharp.  They will come just in range.  If you play in 3rd person like I do as soon as you see the target ring in your view they are in range.  Also remember if they are hitting you it is cause they are either too fast, or not behind you they are coming at an angle.  When you do a turn to get them in range do not do the next turn till you are sure they have come in line behind you not slightly to the right or left behind you but looking at the back of your head.  You will find that you are being hit more when they are at an angle behing you.  </span></td>
